1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,544
OpenHands CLI Primitives. High-level
commands for demo recording.

2
00:00:06,355 --> 00:00:16,819
Recording OpenHands CLI demos used to
require complex keystroke sequences.
Manual typing, waiting for startup, timing
AI responses.

3
00:00:17,633 --> 00:00:28,241
Now demorec supports high-level
primitives. Install, Start, Prompt,
WaitForReady, and Quit. Each handles the
complexity internally.

4
00:00:29,058 --> 00:00:36,546
Here's an example script. One line per
action. No keystroke details to worry
about.

5
00:00:37,352 --> 00:00:39,584
Let's see it in action.

6
00:00:41,082 --> 00:00:44,250
First, let's look at this demo script.

7
00:00:51,870 --> 00:00:55,758
Notice the openhands submode and the
high-level commands.

8
00:00:56,640 --> 00:01:00,768
The Install command runs uv tool install
openhands.

9
00:01:29,026 --> 00:01:32,794
Start launches the CLI and waits for it to
be ready.

10
00:01:53,650 --> 00:01:56,530
Prompt sends our message to the AI.

11
00:02:07,400 --> 00:02:11,792
WaitForReady polls the terminal until the
AI finishes responding.

12
00:04:09,847 --> 00:04:14,887
The AI responded. WaitForReady detected
when it was done.

13
00:04:14,888 --> 00:04:18,512
Finally, Quit exits the CLI cleanly.

14
00:04:19,800 --> 00:04:28,296
OpenHands CLI Primitives. Available now in
demorec. Check out the repo and try it on
your next demo.

